p://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1367<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/03 7:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ~</span><hr size=1> Buy a ToD, fungi tunic, bandage summoning thingy, snare whip, and a high Dps weapon. With those you will become the second ( er make that third nowadays ) worst soloing class in everquest. <br>
<br>
Warriors suck at soloing cause the best ways of soloing involve not getting hit, something I have found to be near impossible to reproduce multiple fights in a row <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=abynormal777>abynormal777</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/25/03 7:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   soloing warrior</span><hr size=1> With a fungi and good ac gear (just over 1k with defensive skills maxed) I was able to solo fairly easily to the mid 40's.  Since then I've found a good group that's on almost every time I am so I haven't done much soloing.  Still, I have done some and it seems like up until lvl 50 my equipment was fine for soloing.  I think if I can get my ac over 1100 I can solo into 52 or 53 fairly well.<br>
<br>
So, you should be able to solo effectively until around 50 if you have the plat for good equipment (I spent about 150k - mainly for the fungi and CoCW)...after that it seems to get much harder.<br>
<br>
Abinormal<br>
Often confused troll warrior <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scarsoulklaw>ScarSoulKlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/25/03 8:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ~</span><hr size=1> You can solo successfully up to level 60, with some decent equipment, a little luck and not much downtime.<br>
<br>
The biggest trick is to pick the right mobs - melee only and small agro radius.  Find a nice quiet spot away from the &quot;hot xp&quot; places and you'll do much better since group &quot;X&quot; will not be pulling trains over you every 5 minutes.  They aren't always easy to find, but such places are out there.  <br>
<br>
Based on procs, these are helpful items and not very expensive to put together:<br>
<br>
ToD for slows<br>
Quested sword from Sanctu Seru (can't remember the name but procs a melee debuff and is pretty easy to get)<br>
Snare Whip or Kunzar for snare (Kunzar adds a 110pt DoT which helps)<br>
Treant Staff for Root (escape tool or for quick heal breaks)<br>
Polished Obsidian Great Axe (for attempts at Fear Kiting or just to drive a mob off long enough to get out of there)<br>
Embalmer's knife (bandages)<br>
BloodFire or similar DoT weapon<br>
Bloodpoints or a Zealot's 2HS or similar weapons (proc  lifetaps)<br>
Worker's SledgeHammer (depending on your race/faction with the Overthere Outpost) for quick escapes<br>
<br>
If you're not at the right level to use these items do some research and find similar items that will work at your level.<br>
<br>
For the actual fight use the biggest, nastiest 2Hx you can find with a good ratio, or use a pair of Bloodpoints.  10/21 with a decent sized lifetap on it isn't bad, or use a Bloodpoint primary and a decent ratio offhand with a big DD proc.<br>
<br>
Fungi Tunic or Iksar BP (Fungi helps during combat or after, Iksar will still help lessen the downtime a bit after a fight) are handy as well.  If not, at least a right-click heal BP is something you should try for.<br>
<br>
Once you turn 61, you won't be doing much soloing anyway.  The mobs that used to give good XP are all light blue now and not worth the effort, and the dark blues from PoP will destroy you in most solo confrontations.<br>
<br>
At 60 though, you can easily solo a lot of decent XP giving mobs and build yourself a nice pile of AA points before going to 61 and beyond.  The bonus is the mob will be waiting for you to loot it before or after the next pull <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
