</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zoushanwarfist>Zoushan Warfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/26/03 9:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  solo warrior tales of woe</span><hr size=1> Yes, warriors can solo but certain things will determine how effective you are. Equipment being the main concern along with anything to lessen the down time be it healing / regen potions, bp click heals. Bind wound should be maxed soon as ya can. It helps big time. <br>
<br>
When selecting a zone to try an solo what you want to look for are melee mobs spaced far enough apart to control aggro. Pull the mob to a safe location to kill it if there are roamers around who will aggro or do it trying to learn how to pull in that zone.  <br>
<br>
Equipment to lessen downtime would be any kind of regeneration. Include an item with aura of battle with a regen item an your halfway there. The rest comes from bind wounding. <br>
<br>
I found in some zones, POP zones mainly, I can take out two light blues before I have to rest or heal up. The exp in some of the zones is awesome even for light blue. I have even taken a light blue right after a dark blue. It all depends on how much my dual welded SODs proc. <br>
<br>
Some folks may discard some of the lower level items due to their lack of &quot;UMPH&quot;. Don't do it. If you can self buff yourself it helps when soloing. The lodi shell boot clicky gives ya a nice 10 ac boost, and the click effects off the cobalt arms and boots help as well as the shrunken gobby head. At 60 last time I looked the cobalt arm lesser shield gave me some nice hp. Don't throw em out. So while it may look weak, every little bit adds up when soloing.<br>
<br>
